body:
@joey001, 

How did you rebase this? It should not normally contain everyone's commits... Right now it looks like 18 people participated in the implementation of Affinity Propagation :)

Also a common practice is to write a "PR updated" comment after adding something to your pull request. That way people will be notified and will review your changes asap. If you don't comment, you run the risk of having your PR hang in here longer ;)

In general I think we should discuss whether we make Gabor's GSoC project part of the core streaming API or have them separately in a streaming windowing statistics package or even maven module. For this specific change I am personally ambivalent whether we should have this in core.

@rmetzger: Good point with JIRA. There is no ticket yet for Gabor's work, I'll discuss the issues he is addressing later this week and we will break it up to a number of issues.
@ggevay: The refactor suggestion of yours is desirable. Let us make sure to sit together in person later this week now that my trip to Budapest is confirmed.

I added a test for the FileStateHandle with HDFS, and I also added a commit that fixes an unrelated (but important) issue to the end. 

I would like to merge this soon, so we can build on it afterwards.

@StephanEwen @rmetzger could you guys take a quick look? It's straightforward I guess...
